&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;base-markdown&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At IEM, we’re not just building innovative electrical distribution systems, we’re shaping the future. IEM is dedicated to delivering world-class solutions for complex power needs. After 75 years, we continue to push the boundaries of what’s possible. Whether you’re an experienced professional or just starting out, you’ll have the opportunity to contribute, grow, and make a lasting impact on industries that power the world’s most dynamic markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Demand Planner supports the enterprise demand planning process by developing, maintaining, and refining product-level and customer-level demand forecasts. This role works closely with the Demand Planning Manager and collaborates with Sales to ensure accurate and timely demand signals flow into the S&amp;amp;OP process, enabling effective supply planning and inventory management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain statistical demand forecasts at the product, customer, and regional level using ERP and forecasting tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales team members to gather market intelligence, customer insights, and promotional plans that inform and improve forecast accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the monthly S&amp;amp;OP demand review process, preparing forecast inputs, variance analyses, and supporting documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor forecast accuracy and bias at assigned product/customer levels; identify root causes of forecast error and implement corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clean and accurate demand data within the ERP system, including item-level planning parameters and historical demand records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support new product introduction (NPI) planning by developing initial demand assumptions in coordination with Sales and the Demand Planning Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate regular demand planning reports and dashboards to communicate forecast status and KPI performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify demand trends, seasonality, and anomalies; escalate significant demand shifts to the Demand Planning Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Supply Planning to communicate demand changes that may impact supply feasibility or inventory levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned by supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competencies:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical Skills: Ability to work with data to develop, analyze, and refine statistical forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to Detail: High level of accuracy in maintaining demand data, planning parameters, and forecast records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication Skills: Ability to effectively engage with Sales and cross-functional teams to gather inputs and communicate forecast status.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizational Skills: Ability to manage multiple product lines, customers, and deadlines simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability: Comfortable adjusting forecasts and priorities in response to changing market conditions and business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous Improvement: Willingness to learn and apply new forecasting methods, tools, and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Supply Chain Management, Business, Operations, or a related field required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 2 years of experience in demand planning, forecasting, or supply chain in a manufacturing or industrial environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with ERP systems required; INFOR/SyteLine exper

